to write about

44:07.245 --> 44:09.013 align:left position:37.5%,start line:93.33% size:62.5%
it.

44:09.046 --> 44:12.817 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
And, you know, even though it
seems odd, it
ended up being that that moment
became the

44:12.850 --> 44:17.355 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
genesis of this picture book,
the idea of
the weight of being named after
your father

44:17.388 --> 44:21.092 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
and what happens when you don't
want to be
named after him anymore. What
happens when

44:21.125 --> 44:25.630 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
you want to turn away from his
legacy and
create your own, even when
you're 5 years

44:25.663 --> 44:26.631 align:left position:37.5%,start line:93.33% size:62.5%
old?

44:26.664 --> 44:28.099 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
JEFFREY BROWN: Yes. And that's
what this is.

44:28.132 --> 44:33.404 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
So, it's a young boy, Thunder
Boy Jr., son
of Thunder Boy Sr., right?

44:33.437 --> 44:34.772 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
SHERMAN ALEXIE: Yes.

44:34.805 --> 44:37.375 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
JEFFREY BROWN: Saying, I want --
